snippet.description:

PROMO CODE: UNBOXBYLT

Powerbeats Pro (USA Link) - https://amzn.to/2DZovIk
Powerbeats Pro (International) - https://geni.us/IKYszC

Can the Beats by Dre Powerbeats Pro dethrone the Apple AirPods 2? AirPods have been a popular choice for fully wireless earbuds but for many they aren't secure enough. Powerbeats Pro aims to fix that by including a secure fit and ear hook on each earbud. Powerbeats Pro appear to be targeted at the fitness market featuring water and sweat resistance. So which will it be for you, Powerbeats Pro vs Apple AirPods 2?

Powerbeats Pro aims to fix that by including a secure fit and ear hook on each earbud. Powerbeats Pro appear to be targeted at the fitness market featuring water and sweat resistance. So which will it be for you, Powerbeats Pro vs Apple AirPods 2?

snippet.textDisplay: Yeahhh, dave usually knows his business when it comes to an accurate review but the MSI GS65 felt like garbage all the way around. The only gaming/editing laptop I would recommend buying (that was comparable to the GS65) out of the MSI 2019 lineup would be the MSI p15 Prestige/Creator models. Materials manufacturing was that much better on the p15 vs. The GS65s flubberized feel. The only caveat being the trackpad (extremely responsive compared to dragging your finger across the GS65) so long as you don't mind the built-in fingerprint reader eating up a good portion of the upper left hand side,  I had zero palm rejection - Granted most gamers (and even) creators use a mouse these days given newer laptop specs.

snippet.textDisplay: Personally, the thing that bother me about these head phones are, I find them heavy and tight, the clicking sound from the button on the right ear cup is loud and harsh, quite unpleasant. I work as an at home customer service rep, to avoid neck pain from holding phone between my head and shoulder, I got them thinking they would be great to use at work. But I believe because there is no cord, using them for phone calls make you voice sound far away and distorted to the person your speaking with, so no good, and again they're tight and heavy making them uncomfortable to wear for long period of time. They are  really beautiful, I love the color, I got the light blue, and the sound is great for music and tv shows I watch on my phone and laptop. I just wish I did not have the other issues using them. I would not buy these if I could go back in time.

snippet.textDisplay: WARNING: These headphones have an extremely thin (2mm) and flimsy plastic point of failure at the top of the slider (See Part six at @t. Once this plastic cracks (and it did for me with a little over a year of casual use) the entire earcup will fall off the headphones and be supported by nothing other than a wire. Incidentally, once the earcup falls off, you can also see that it is only held on by a tiny piece of bent metal. Do not believe the hype. These headphones - and unless they fixed this flaw in the 1000XM4 as well - are flimsy and not worth your money.

Can you believe that my dad gave me this when I asked for a wacom when I appplied to university (design), and I had to put on the fakest smile ever for him because this is the most expensive piece of shit I have ever owned. Is well made, serves its purpose and it can be useful if you need to constantly take notes and/or you are eccentric as fuck; but beyond that is useless. When you move a sketch to your computer is impossible to work with.
P.S: We don't have much money (it is worse when you take into account the change from dollars to pesos), and I feel frustated (because now I don't have money to buy a decent pen tablet) and ungrateful everytime I put my eyes on it.

I use it everyday and after a year, it still works and looks like brand new 😯

snippet.textDisplay: To much hate for apple LoL, if you are into taking pictures and videos to do something with it ..apple is great for that. And is true, apple takes long to give their consumers something like OLED displays who are ven found un sub $500 android phones. But most Apple users just want the same but better and that is taking better pictures & videos.  Now for regular aka average users who are not a photo or video tech enthusiasts and never ever will use their phones to their full potential and who take an average looking non staged selfies & video for Instagram, Facebook, or Tiktok, having a midrange android or used apple phone would be great! More and more I find new top of the line apple phones less attractive to say a Poco f2 pro. Why Cause I don't give rats @$$ about games like Fornite and the likes or a perfect picture or video that was taken on the dark (wife has a pixel and is great for that). My main concern is,  can I get a big nice-looking screen over 6 inches, and with no notch if possible to watch Netflix and youtube ?? and not over $550. Ohhh look all these other android phones can give me that ...yes, please !!! And this coming from a still iP7+ user who just ordered the POCO f2 pro ..(because it has no notch!).  As the years go by the picture and video will be almost super great quality on most phones so ...in the meantime, big apple rules the camera and video thing, and the pixel is second IMO. OK NERDS time for me to go to sleep.

snippet.textDisplay:
These have had pretty major issues with software over the past few months. There was a recent firmware update that bricked headphones showing a flashing red and white light which seems to have affected quite a few users. I had to get mine replaced because of this.

I couldn't connect using straight Bluetooth until I'd done the initial setup with the Bose app... Both pairs I've owned took at least 30 mins of restarting/uninstalling/force quitting to finally be recognised in the android app. No rhyme or reason why they suddenly decided to connect. Luckily after the initial set up you can uninstall the app and they'll connect normally via Bluetooth.

They also stutter when you have two devices connected like they can't decide what source they want to use.

Definitely wish that I'd avoided these. So disappointing coming from the SoundTrue's and QC35's.

snippet.textDisplay: Bought the smaller version last week.  Impressive sound for a pint sized speaker.  Would have been nice to include an equalizer app to tone down the bass a little.  Pretty solid feel and build quality (except for awkward and clumsy micro-usb port and its' annoying cover) but not something I would take to a party or event.  Plays a cool sound on start up and shut down.  Shuts down automatically after about 5 minutes of non-use.  Sound is mostly balanced, regardless of positioning.  Dropped it twice.  Once from a night stand (2 ft) onto carpet, and once from the counter (3ft) onto tiled floor...no noticable damage.  I think it's also somewhat waterproof but not submersible. $65.  Perfect for quiet night viewing tv or listening to music.  Easier to control volume with tv remote or phone.

I do not recommend this phone.

I bought mine in the UK. In one month and a half after my purchase dead pixels appeared on my screen and the screen now flashes.

The experience with Samsung Customer Service is terrible.
The call centre person said that will contact you the next day, but after my call I discovered that the person would not work the next 4 consecutive days and no other colleague knows what was discussed.

Having to explain the situation dozens of times .

Also, each Samsung employee gives a different answer. There is inconsistency in the information provided to the client.

I am really disappointed with Samsung.
